⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Continuing the Quincy cocktail tour with a stop at @victorypointmb ! Exploring what Quincy has to offer with @discoverquincy is turning out to be one of the highlights of my summer! @victorypointmb has some of best views of the water and some great drinks to take in the sights and skyline. By now I think you’ve guessed it: I’m giving away a $50 giftcard to @victorypointmb 🙌🏾🎉💰. My five favorite drinks are: the VP Coco Punch, Aperol Spritz, Stoli Doli, Red Sangria, and Lavazza Martini (all pictured in that order 😉)⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

node.text: We’re taking cocktails to new levels this year. Sea level that is. This week I got to ‘drive the boat’ with @bostonelectricboats and had a blast. They’re located in India Wharf Marina right next to the New England Aquarium. You can enjoy a boat ride on the harbor…and yes…you can drive and be your own captain 😉🛥. You can book a boat ride for up to twelve people and have the time of your life. Do what I did: I booked with them and gave a cocktail class on board to some of my close friends and we toasted martinis into the sunset…literally. By the way, stay tuned since I’ll be doing a little giveaway this Friday to help you get out on the water and be your own captain. Check out www.electricboatsboston.com for more info and to book! Tell them I sent you 😉🛥. #nailthecocktail

🍓1 part Sipsmith London Dry Gin
🍓3 parts premium tonic water (or soda water for a G&S)
🍓Freshly sliced strawberries and lime garnish
